# ============================================================
# CHLOE ALPHA — PROJECT RULES FOR CURSOR
# ============================================================
# DO NOT MODIFY CHLOE'S CORE ENGINE BEHAVIOR.
# DO NOT MODIFY TRADING LOGIC UNLESS EXPLICITLY INSTRUCTED.
# DO NOT TOUCH SANITY GATES, RISK ENGINE, OR SWARM LOGIC.
# DASHBOARD IS READ-ONLY — NEVER EXECUTE TRADES OR MODIFY CONFIGS.
# ============================================================

# ------------------------
# PROJECT ARCHITECTURE
# ------------------------
Chloe Alpha is a multi-module quant trading engine.

ROOT DIRECTORY:
- engine_alpha/

CORE SUBSYSTEMS (DO NOT BREAK):
- engine_alpha/core/               (Chloe's brain, decision logic)
- engine_alpha/loop/               (run_step_live, execution, risk gates)
- engine_alpha/reflect/            (nightly research, weighted analyzer/tuner)
- engine_alpha/risk/               (PF, DD, sanity gates, autoscaler)
- engine_alpha/mirror/             (wallet inference, mirror engine)
- engine_alpha/swarm/              (supervisory system: sentinel/audit/challenger)
- engine_alpha/exchange/           (paper & real exchange clients)
- engine_alpha/config/             (wallets, thresholds, gates, config_loader)

DATA PATHS (DO NOT CHANGE):
- reports/
- reports/research/
- logs/
- data/ohlcv/

IMPORTANT FILES (ALWAYS EXISTING):
- reports/pf_local.json
- reports/loop_health.json
- reports/research/hybrid_research_dataset.parquet
- reports/research/multi_horizon_stats.json
- reports/research/strategy_strength.json
- config/confidence_map.json
- config/entry_thresholds.json
- reports/research/swarm_audit_log.jsonl
- reports/research/swarm_research_verifier.jsonl
- reports/research/swarm_challenger_log.jsonl
- reports/research/swarm_sentinel_report.json

# -----------------------------------------------
# DASHBOARD RULES — STREAMLIT QUANT DASHBOARD
# -----------------------------------------------
The dashboard lives under:
- engine_alpha/dashboard/

ENTRY POINT:
- engine_alpha/dashboard/dashboard.py

PANELS (each has its own render()):
- home_panel.py
- live_panel.py
- research_panel.py
- swarm_panel.py
- risk_panel.py
- wallet_panel.py
- operator_panel.py
- system_panel.py

SHARED COMPONENTS:
- engine_alpha/dashboard/components/

RULES:
- The dashboard is STRICTLY READ-ONLY.
- Dashboard MUST NOT place trades, alter configs, or call trading functions.
- Dashboard reads JSON, Parquet, or logs only.
- Visual improvements are allowed (charts, heatmaps, tables).
- New panels must follow the modular structure: file with render().

# -----------------------------------------------
# WHAT CURSOR MUST NEVER MODIFY
# -----------------------------------------------
- Any trading logic under engine_alpha/loop/
- gate_and_size_trade(), sanity gates, risk_autoscaler
- execute_trade logic
- run_step_live logic (unless explicitly requested)
- nightly research pipeline output structures
- SWARM supervisory modules (sentinel, audit loop, research verifier, challenger)
- wallet system & exchange client logic
- PF or DD computation
- mirror engine
- file paths used by analyzer/tuner/research

# -----------------------------------------------
# ALLOWED MODIFICATIONS
# -----------------------------------------------
Cursor MAY:
- Improve dashboard visuals
- Add new dashboard panels
- Interpret and visualize Chloe's data files
- Extend `tools/` scripts when instructed
- Add helper utilities that do NOT affect core trading

Cursor MAY NOT:
- Change data schemas for analyzer/tuner
- Change JSON formats in reports/
- Change threshold or PF logic automatically
- Add hidden side effects to read-only panels

# -----------------------------------------------
# HOW TO ASK FOR HELP (GUIDELINES FOR THE USER)
# -----------------------------------------------
When requesting code updates:
- Be explicit about the file and panel you want changed.
- Say "Dashboard only, read-only" to avoid affecting the engine.
- For logic changes, specify exact modules you want adjusted.

# -----------------------------------------------
# END — CHLOE ALPHA PROJECT RULESET
# -----------------------------------------------


